Jenner first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Jenner had a population of 122. The population density was {{convert|57.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Jenner was 94 (77.0%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.8%) [[African Americans|African American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 7 (5.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 2 (1.6%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 18 (14.8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 14 persons (11.5%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Jenner CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0637274 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 22, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 80 households, out of which 6 (7.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 27 (33.8%) were married-couple households, 6 (7.5%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 25 (31.3%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 22 (27.5%) had a male householder with no partner present. 29 households (36.2%) were one person, and 18 (22.5%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.52.<ref name=DP1/> There were 42 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (52.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Jenner CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0637274 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 22, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 5 people (4.1%) under the age of 18, 1 person (0.8%) aged 18 to 24, 19 people (15.6%) aged 25 to 44, 42 people (34.4%) aged 45 to 64, and 55 people (45.1%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 63.8{{nbsp}}years. There were 58 males and 64 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 161 housing units at an average density of {{convert|76.3|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 80 (49.7%) were occupied. Of these, 63 (78.8%) were owner-occupied, and 17 (21.3%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>
